cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the design of wireless queueing network control policies. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the design of cost functions for wireless networks with streaming media traffic. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a control framework for wireless networks. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper considers the reduction of buffer underflows in case of streaming traffic. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security issues in wireless networks.
